au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.filenamer
Class AbstractFileNamer

java.lang.Object
  au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.filenamer.AbstractFileNamer
Direct Known Subclasses:
DefaultFileNamer
public abstract class AbstractFileNamer
extends java.lang.Object

This is an abstract class to represent a Xena FileNamer. It's primary purpose is to create output files using a naming scheme that can be implemented by a specific institution.

makeNewXenaFile

public java.io.File makeNewXenaFile(XenaInputSource xis,
                                    AbstractNormaliser normaliser)
                             throws XenaException
Make a new Xena File using the destination directory as set in the FileNamerManager. This is the preferred method for creating new Xena files. This method actually calls makeNewXenaFile(XenaInputSource input, AbstractNormaliser normaliser, File destinationDir) and simply passes it's arguments to it, along with the destination directory obtained from the fileNamerManager.

Parameters:
xis - - Input Xena Input source
normaliser - - The normaliser that is being used during normalisation.
Returns:
File - the new Xena File.
Throws:
XenaException - 0 in the case of the Xena file not being able to be created.
See Also:
AbstractFileNamer.makeNewXenaFile(XenaInputSource input, AbstractNormaliser normaliser, File destinationDir)

makeNewXenaFile

public abstract java.io.File makeNewXenaFile(XenaInputSource input,
                                             AbstractNormaliser normaliser,
                                             java.io.File destinationDir)
                                      throws XenaException
This abstract method creates a new Xena file. This must be implemented by any concrete file namers. The concrete implmentation must create a file, based on some or all of the inputs (or none if you like!). A XenaException should be thrown in the case of the file not being able to be created. Additionally, the flag 'overwrite' may be interrogated or ignored depending on the implementation of the specific fileNamer.

Parameters:
input -
normaliser -
destinationDir -
Returns:
File - the new Xena file.
Throws:
XenaException - - in the event of an error creating the file.
